:Theme_DivineVsMortalCondition a :Theme,
        owl:NamedIndividual ;
    :description "Contrast between gods (and god-born) and mortals; warning against claiming godlike status in suffering or honour."^^xsd:string .

:Theme_LivingDeathAndExile a :Theme,
        owl:NamedIndividual ;
    :description "Antigone is led to a tomb while alive, describing herself as a metic among neither living nor dead."^^xsd:string .

:Theme_FamilyCurseOfLabdacids a :Theme,
        owl:NamedIndividual ;
    :description "The inherited ruin of Oedipus' house: maternal bed-curses, incest, and the ancestral doom of the Labdacids."^^xsd:string .

